node.doctext:
Look into thy past. Where hast thou judged?
<br><br>
[%
use Everything::Experience;
return "Spirits flee!" if $$USER{title} eq "Guest User";

my $userVoteCount = $DB->sqlSelect("COUNT(*)", "vote,writeup", "vote.vote_id=writeup.writeup_id AND vote.voter_user=$$USER{node_id}");
my $userUpvoteCount = $DB->sqlSelect("COUNT(*)", "vote,writeup", "vote.vote_id=writeup.writeup_id AND vote.voter_user=$$USER{node_id} AND weight>0");

if ($userVoteCount == 0)
{
  return "..thou art too young yet. Come back soon." if getLevel($USER) == 0;
  return "Thou hast grown, but are still yet a man. Prove thy judgment!";
}

my $totalVoteCount = $DB->sqlSelect("COUNT(vote_id)", "vote,writeup", "vote.vote_id=writeup.writeup_id");
my $userVotePercentage = sprintf("%.4f", 100*($userVoteCount / $totalVoteCount));
my $userUpvotePercentage = sprintf("%.3f", 100*($userUpvoteCount / $userVoteCount));

my $totalWriteupCount = $DB->sqlSelect("COUNT(writeup_id)","writeup");
my $unvotableWriteupCount = $DB->sqlSelect("COUNT(*)", "writeup,node", "node.node_id=writeup.writeup_id AND (wrtype_writeuptype=177599 OR author_user=$$USER{node_id})");
$totalWriteupCount -= $unvotableWriteupCount;
my $userWriteupVotePercentage = sprintf("%.3f", 100*($userVoteCount / $totalWriteupCount));

return "Thou hast cast $userVoteCount votes... $userVotePercentage\% of the judgements made of all time, across $userWriteupVotePercentage\% of all votable writeups. Of these, $userUpvotePercentage\% are upvotes.";
%]
<hr />
<p><small>Keep in mind, these numbers could be wildly inaccurate. Oracles aren't known for their precision.</small></p>
<p>How is this different from [Voting Oracle]?</p>
<ul>
<li>It only includes votes for existing/published writeups. The vote table might still hold votes for deleted writeups, and unpublished drafts.</li>
<li>It ignores the [definition] writeuptype rather than only ignoring Webster 1913 writeups. There are thousands of writeups that are unvoteable definitions that weren't created by Webby.</li>
<li>It ignores your own writeups since you can't vote on them.</li>
</ul>
